The paper deals with the problem of generating video sequences, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model uses 3D convolutions, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper evaluates its model on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in graphics (cs.GR) research.
